B. What factors impact the delayed luggage MBR?
   1. Focus on two types of flights
         a. Short connections
               - Focus on the passengers who had connecting flights
               - Define a short connection as anyone 
                        catching a domestic flight <45 minutes from the arrival of their flight
                        catching an internation flight <90 minutes from the arrival of their flight
               - Possible that the passenger had time to make the connection but the bag didn't
         b. Delays leading to short or missed connections (D0)
                - Possible that the passenger had time to make the connection but the bag didn't
   2. Human error
      - Quality of training- training feedback questionaires
      - Not reading tags properly, bags ending up on wrong flights or not flight at all
      - Bag room not dropping off bags in appropriate time
      - Transfer runners not picking up backs in appropriate time to bring to connecting flights
C. What factors impact the damaged luggage?
   1. Mishandled baggage by ramp crew/ transfer runners/ bag room?
      - Rushing (falling off of beltloaders/ bag carts/ piers)
      - Carelessness (not taking care of bags. Not closing bag carts so bags fall off) 
